				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MT group bard role in raid<a name="32949"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 11:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It depends on the mob.  I will say I would use Psalm of Veeshan before any of the rhythms line no matter what mob we were fighting.  Seriously, with a 2.8 mod, puretone or Thunderous Drums, Guardian Rhythms does 104 or 105 MR - assuming no IM.  Psalm of Veeshan with puretone does something like 210 to ALL resists.  Why on earth would you choose Guardian Rhythms over Psalm of Veeshan?  In my personal situation, with a Shadowsong Cloak, IM3, SM2, and JF2, PoV is even more likely to be the first choice any time we need resists.
<br />

<br />
But it does depend on the mob.  For Rydda'Dar, I twist Niv's Harmonic, charisma, and Psalm of Veeshan.  All 3 are singing based and I can generate a 3.3 mod without going to puretone even.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
