			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MT group bard role in raid<a name="33454"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 04 5:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Charisma does increase the chance that DI will go off and save the life of a player that may otherwise die.  I realize that at first glance, this seems like a minor, low probability thing that would seldom save a raid.  But the fact is, in POP and GoD, the mobs hit so hard that it is really easy for them to get a lucky triple or quad for full damage and take out a tank in one hit.  It may only happen once a fight, but if it does, then you want to maximize the probability that you will counter the mobs good luck with a bit of your own and have your main tank go from very-nearly-dead to CH status in a second.  Raising their Charisma as high as possible is the key.  I know it seems silly at first glance, but in POP and GoD boss fights, I see DI go off nearly every fight.  I saw a Rydda'Dar fight where it went off 5 times - 3 warriors, myself, and one cleric in my group, all of whom were getting rampage at various times in the fight - all saved by DI.  I was singing Solon's in that group with SM2, JF2, Shadowsong Cloak harmonize, and the Crowned Staff of Anguish. All 6 of us had CHA over 250 and 4 of the group were at 305.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
