				<td colspan="2"><span>I could be wrong but am pretty sure that Jam Fest doesn't affect charisma or niv's harmonic?
<br />

<br />
Voice mod does though, and amplification makes a huge difference until you get a high enough voice mod without it... Which I guess is when you get a songblade bascially.
<br />

<br />
I tend to load&quot;
<br />

<br />
nivs
<br />
charmisa
<br />
psalm of veeshan
<br />
amp
<br />
call of the muse
<br />
mana
<br />
hos 
<br />
mez 
<br />

<br />
for the main tank group, and for named fights use 
<br />

<br />
amp
<br />
nivs harmonic
<br />
charmisa
<br />
veeshan
<br />

<br />
I find it hard to keep 4 up in a raid, so I do this kind of alternating thing with amplification and one of the songs, letting the other song drop once every two rounds. Which song I let drop, is actually something I wouldnt mind some input on....
<br />

<br />
Do you let charmisa drop, betting that di won't fire for those 18 seconds?
<br />

<br />
Do you let ac drop, betting that di will &quot;save&quot; the tank if necessary in those 18 seconds? 
<br />

<br />
Do you let veeshan drop?
<br />

<br />
If the fight doesn't rely on resists then its easy: drop veeshan. Otherwise, I tend to be undecided; for a while I let charisma go, then I started letting ac go, but I still haven't made up my mind which is the better choice.
<br />

<br />
Does anyone else ponder this, or is it just me? Sometimes I do think these bard decisions are 6 of oen and half a dozen of the other...haven't you ever seen those fights where all the tanks with the bard die, and the tank without the bard wins the fight?
<br />

<br />
I leave muse up for the clearing of trash. I've always thought, maybe the healers in the goup might want to nuke something.</span></td>
