				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MT group bard role in raid<a name="34804"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 15 04 11:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I ponder it, believe me.
<br />

<br />
Here's my take on it -- with Niv's, you're adding 100 AC on top of a tank who already has at least 1500-1600 AC if not more.  Your 100 AC helps but it isn't the &quot;make or break&quot; factor that Charisma would be on DI or resists would be on a DD or DoT hitting the tank.
<br />

<br />
In other words, the significance of 100 more AC on a 1600 AC warrior is what -- 7 or 8 percent of their AC?
<br />

<br />
Wheras your 100+ Charisma added to their 140 charisma with buff may actually be 30 to 50% of their total charisma.
<br />

<br />
And your 275 added resists on top of the 200 or so they have unbuffed is like 60 to 70% of their resist total.
<br />

<br />
So if it was me, I would let Niv's drop.  That is going to have the least detrimental effect overall on your tank, as I see it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
